mTADA was applied to DNM datasets of 15 pairs of six disorders: five neuropsychiatric disorders including DD, ID, ASD, SCZ, EE; and CHD. These DNMs were classified into different categories using annotation tools. Based on previous results10,22, we used loss of function (LoF), missense damaging (MiD) DNMs for all disorders and also added synonymous DNMs within DNase I hypersensitive sites for SCZ (Methods). We defined the gene-level genetic overlap (gO) of two disorders as: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
